column3: Eo Tyr is looking particularly pleased with themself.
Oooh, sapling of the king! I have a fascinating delight to show you.
...But he seems to have wandered off somewhere. Could you look for him, please?
And when I say “him” I mean...Another Anden. You'll know him once you find him─you'll see!
He can't have gone far. Go on, go on! Find Another Anden.
This loitering lump of leaves looks strikingly like an Anden you once knew. Perhaps this is what Eo Tyr is seeking.
This leafman is straining to communicate, but unlike Anden, it seems incapable of speech.
Now, I have prepared this sweet shrublet for a very special reason. Will you hear it?
As long as I have known him, I have always, <Emphasis>always</Emphasis> longed to speak with Anden. Oooh, how I hoped and pined.
Then suddenly, my wish came true! Now here I am, spending day after day talking and laughing and playing with you both. I don't think any pixie has ever known such fun.
That is why I wish to repay your kindness with a little gift─not a talking leafman, but a <Emphasis>walking</Emphasis> leafman! His name is “Anden III.”

I borrowed some of Original Anden's leaves after pruning him.
Twist a branch here, nip a bud there─and there you have it! Oooh, isn't he adorable? Your very own Personal Anden!
Speaking of personal, I mustn't keep you long, lest the king think I'm trying to steal away their precious sapling.
As though I would, when I have Anden. Oooh, Anden!
